## How Browser Memory Management Works

Modern browsers use **automatic garbage collection** (GC) to manage memory. The most common approach is **mark-and-sweep**:

1. **Mark phase**: Starting from "roots" (global objects, active call stack), the GC traverses all reachable objects
2. **Sweep phase**: Any unmarked objects are considered garbage and freed

Most browsers also use **generational collection**, where:
- New objects are in "young generation" (collected frequently)
- Surviving objects move to "old generation" (collected less often)

